1.name: Account
1.desc: Account mnemonic as agreed between broker and institution.

3.name: AdvRefID
3.desc: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE transaction types.

6.name: AvgPx
6.desc: Calculated average price of all fills on this order.

7.name: BeginSeqNo
7.desc: Message sequence number of first record in range to be resent

8.name: BeginString
8.desc: Identifies beginning of new message and protocol version. ALWAYS THE FIRST FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted)

9.name: BodyLength
9.desc: Message length, in bytes, is verified by counting the number of characters in the message following the BodyLength (9) field up to, and including, the delimiter immediately preceding the CheckSum (10) field. ALWAYS SECOND FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted) For example, for message 8=FIX 4.4^9=5^35=0^10=10^, the BodyLength is 5 for 35=0^

10.name: CheckSum
10.desc: Three byte, simple checksum (see Appendix B of FIX Specification for description). ALWAYS THE LAST FIELD IN RECORD; i.e. serves, with the trailing <SOH>, as the end-of-record delimiter. Always defined as three characters. (Always unencrypted)

11.name: ClOrdID
11.desc: Unique identifier for Order as assigned by institution. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms which electronically submit multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the ClOrdID (11) field to assure uniqueness across days.

12.name: Commission
12.desc: Commission. Note if CommType is percentage, Commission of 5% should be represented as .05.

15.name: Currency
15.desc: Identifies currency used for price. Absence of this field is interpreted as the default for the security. It is recommended that systems provide the currency value whenever possible.

16.name: EndSeqNo
16.desc: Message sequence number of last record in range to be resent. If request is for a single record BeginSeqNo (7) = EndSeqNo (16) . If request is for all messages subsequent to a particular message, EndSeqNo (16) = '999999'

17.name: ExecID
17.desc: Unique identifier of Execution Report (8) message as assigned by broker (will be 0 (zero) for ExecTransType (20) =3 (Status)).

18.name: ExecInst
18.desc: Instructions for order handling on exchange trading floor. If more than one instruction is applicable to an order, this field can contain multiple instructions separated by space.

19.name: ExecRefID
19.desc: Reference identifier used with Cancel and Correct transaction types.

21.name: HandlInst
21.desc: Instructions for order handling on Broker trading floor

23.name: IOIid
23.desc: Unique identifier of Indication of Interest (6) message.

24.name: IOIOthSvc
24.desc: Indicates if, and on which other services, the indication has been advertised. Each character represents an additional service (e.g. if on Bridge and Autex, field = BA, if only on Autex, field = A)

26.name: IOIRefID
26.desc: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE, transaction types.

27.name: IOIShares
27.desc: Number of shares in numeric or relative size.

28.name: IOITransType
28.desc: Identifies Indication of Interest (6) message transaction type

30.name: LastMkt
30.desc: Market of execution for last fill

31.name: LastPx
31.desc: Price of this (last) fill. Field not required for ExecTransType (20) = 3 (Status)

32.name: LastShares
32.desc: Quantity of shares bought/sold on this (last) fill. Field not required for ExecTransType (20) = 3 (Status)

33.name: LinesOfText
33.desc: Identifies number of lines of text body

35.name: MsgType
35.desc: Defines message type. ALWAYS THE THIRD FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted)

37.name: OrderID
37.desc: Unique identifier for Order as assigned by broker. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms which accept multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the OrderID (37) field to assure uniqueness across days.

41.name: OrigClOrdID
41.desc: ClOrdID (11) of the previous order (NOT the initial order of the day) as assigned by the institution, used to identify the previous order in cancel and cancel/replace requests.

42.name: OrigTime
42.desc: Time of message origination (always expressed in GMT)

43.name: PossDupFlag
43.desc: Indicates possible retransmission of message with this sequence number

46.name: RelatdSym
46.desc: Symbol of issue related to story. Can be repeated within message to identify multiple companies.

47.name: Rule80A
47.desc: Note that the name of this field is changing to 'OrderCapacity' as Rule80A is a very US market-specific term. Other world markets need to convey similar information, however, often a subset of the US values. See the 'Rule80A (aka OrderCapacity) Usage by Market' appendix of FIX Specification for market-specific usage of this field.

48.name: SecurityID
48.desc: CUSIP or other alternate security identifier

49.name: SenderCompID
49.desc: Assigned value used to identify firm sending message.

50.name: SenderSubID
50.desc: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator (desk, trader, etc.)

52.name: SendingTime
52.desc: Time of message transmission (always expressed in GMT)

56.name: TargetCompID
56.desc: Assigned value used to identify receiving firm.

57.name: TargetSubID
57.desc: Assigned value used to identify specific individual or unit intended to receive message. 'ADMIN' reserved for administrative messages not intended for a specific user.

58.name: Text
58.desc: Free format text string (Note: this field does not have a specified maximum length)

59.name: TimeInForce
59.desc: Specifies how long the order remains in effect. Absence of this field is interpreted as DAY.

60.name: TransactTime
60.desc: Time of execution/order creation (expressed in GMT)

62.name: ValidUntilTime
62.desc: Indicates expiration time of indication message (always expressed in GMT)

63.name: SettlmntTyp
63.desc: Indicates order settlement period. Absence of this field is interpreted as Regular. Regular is defined as the default settlement period for the particular security on the exchange of execution.

64.name: FutSettDate
64.desc: Specific date of trade settlement in YYYYMMDD format. Required when SettlmntTyp (63) = 6 (Future) or SettlmntTyp (63) = 8 (Sellers Option). (expressed in local time at place of settlement)

65.name: SymbolSfx
65.desc: Additional information about the security (e.g. preferred, warrants, etc.). Absence of this field indicates common. Valid values:As defined in the NYSE Stock and bond Symbol Directory and in the AMEXFitch Directory

66.name: ListID
66.desc: Unique identifier for list as assigned by institution, used to associate multiple individual orders. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms which generate multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the ListID (66) field to assure uniqueness across days.

67.name: ListSeqNo
67.desc: Sequence of individual order within list (i.e. ListSeqNo (67) of ListNoOrds (68) , 2 of 25, 3 of 25, . . . )

68.name: ListNoOrds
68.desc: Total number of orders within list (i.e. ListSeqNo (67) of TotNoOrders (68) , e.g. 2 of 25, 3 of 25, . . . )

69.name: ListExecInst
69.desc: Free format text message containing list handling and execution instructions.

72.name: RefAllocID
72.desc: Reference identifier to be used with Replace and Cancel AllocTransType (71) records.

73.name: NoOrders
73.desc: Indicates number of orders to be combined for average pricing and allocation.

74.name: AvgPrxPrecision
74.desc: Indicates number of decimal places to be used for average pricing. Absence of this field indicates that default precision arranged by the broker/institution is to be used.

75.name: TradeDate
75.desc: Indicates date of trade referenced in this record in YYYYMMDD format. Absence of this field indicates current day (expressed in local time at place of trade).

76.name: ExecBroker
76.desc: Identifies executing/give-up broker. Standard NASD market-maker mnemonic is preferred.

78.name: NoAllocs
78.desc: Number of AllocAccount (79) / AllocQty (80) / ProcessCode (81) instances included in allocation record.

80.name: AllocShares
80.desc: Number of shares to be allocated to specific sub-account

81.name: ProcessCode
81.desc: Processing code for sub-account. Absence of this field in AllocAccount (79) / AllocQty (80) / ProcessCode (81) instance indicates regular trade.

82.name: NoRpts
82.desc: Total number of reports within series.

83.name: RptSeq
83.desc: Sequence number of message within report series.

84.name: CxlQty
84.desc: Total number of shares canceled for this order.

93.name: SignatureLength
93.desc: Number of bytes in signature field.

95.name: RawDataLength
95.desc: Number of bytes in raw data field.

96.name: RawData
96.desc: Unformatted raw data, can include bitmaps, word processor documents, etc.

97.name: PossResend
97.desc: Indicates that message may contain information that has been sent under another sequence number.

100.name: ExDestination
100.desc: Execution destination as defined by institution when order is entered.

102.name: CxlRejReason
102.desc: Code to identify reason for cancel rejection.

103.name: OrdRejReason
103.desc: Code to identify reason for order rejection.

104.name: IOIQualifier
104.desc: Code to qualify Indication of Interest (6) use.

105.name: WaveNo
105.desc: Identifier to aid in the management of multiple lists derived from a single, master list.

106.name: Issuer
106.desc: Company name of security issuer (e.g. International Business Machines)

109.name: ClientID
109.desc: Firm identifier used in third party-transactions.

110.name: MinQty
110.desc: Minimum quantity of an order to be executed.

111.name: MaxFloor
111.desc: Maximum number of shares within an order to be shown on the exchange floor at any given time.

112.name: TestReqID
112.desc: Identifier included in Test Request (1) message to be returned in resulting Heartbeat (0)

113.name: ReportToExch
113.desc: Identifies party of trade responsible for exchange reporting.

114.name: LocateReqd
114.desc: Indicates whether the broker is to locate the stock in conjunction with a short sell order.

115.name: OnBehalfOfCompID
115.desc: Assigned value used to identify firm originating message if the message was delivered by a third party i.e. the third party firm identifier would be delivered in the SenderCompID (49) field and the firm originating the message in this field.

116.name: OnBehalfOfSubID
116.desc: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator (i.e. trader) if the message was delivered by a third party

118.name: NetMoney
118.desc: Total amount due as the result of the transaction (e.g. for Buy order - principal + commission + fees) reported in currency of execution.

119.name: SettlCurrAmt
119.desc: Total amount due expressed in settlement currency (includes the effect of the forex transaction)

121.name: ForexReq
121.desc: Indicates request for forex accommodation trade to be executed along with security transaction.

122.name: OrigSendingTime
122.desc: Original time of message transmission (always expressed in GMT) when transmitting orders as the result of a resend request.

123.name: GapFillFlag
123.desc: Indicates that the Sequence Reset (4) message is replacing administrative or application messages which will not be resent.

124.name: NoExecs
124.desc: No of execution record groups to follow.

126.name: ExpireTime
126.desc: Time/Date of order expiration (always expressed in GMT)

128.name: DeliverToCompID
128.desc: Assigned value used to identify the firm targeted to receive the message if the message is delivered by a third party i.e. the third party firm identifier would be delivered in the TargetCompID (56) field and the ultimate receiver firm ID in this field.

129.name: DeliverToSubID
129.desc: Assigned value used to identify specific message recipient (i.e. trader) if the message is delivered by a third party

130.name: IOINaturalFlag
130.desc: Indicates that Indication of Interest (6) is the result of an existing agency order or a facilitation position resulting from an agency order, not from principal trading or order solicitation activity.

136.name: NoMiscFees
136.desc: Number of repeating groups of miscellaneous fees

141.name: ResetSeqNumFlag
141.desc: Indicates that the both sides of the FIX session should reset sequence numbers.

142.name: SenderLocationID
142.desc: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator's location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader)

143.name: TargetLocationID
143.desc: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator's location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader)

144.name: OnBehalfOfLocationID
144.desc: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator's location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader) if the message was delivered by a third party

145.name: DeliverToLocationID
145.desc: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator's location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader) if the message was delivered by a third party

146.name: NoRelatedSym
146.desc: Specifies the number of repeating symbols specified.

147.name: Subject
147.desc: The subject of an Email (C) message

148.name: Headline
148.desc: The headline of a News (B) message

149.name: URLLink
149.desc: A URL (Uniform Resource Locator) link to additional information (i.e. http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uniform_Resource_Locator)

150.name: ExecType
150.desc: Describes the specific Execution Report (8) (i.e. Pending Cancel) while OrdStatus (39) will always identify the current order status (i.e. Partially Filled)

151.name: LeavesQty
151.desc: Amount of shares open for further execution. If the OrdStatus (39) is Canceled, DoneForTheDay, Expired, Calculated, or Rejected (in which case the order is no longer active) then LeavesQty (151) could be 0, otherwise LeavesQty (151) = OrderQty (38) - CumQty (14) .

152.name: CashOrderQty
152.desc: Specifies the approximate order quantity desired in total monetary units vs. as a number of shares. The broker would be responsible for converting and calculating a share quantity ( OrderQty (38) ) based upon this amount to be used for the actual order and subsequent messages.

155.name: SettlCurrFxRate
155.desc: Foreign exchange rate used to compute SettlCurrAmount (119) from Currency (15) to SettlCurrency (120)

156.name: SettlCurrFxRateCalc
156.desc: Specifies whether or not SettlCurrFxRate (155) should be multiplied or divided.

157.name: NumDaysInterest
157.desc: Number of Days of Interest for convertible bonds and fixed income

158.name: AccruedInterestRate
158.desc: Accrued Interest Rate for convertible bonds and fixed income

159.name: AccruedInterestAmt
159.desc: Amount of Accrued Interest for convertible bonds and fixed income

160.name: SettlInstMode
160.desc: Indicates mode used for Settlement Instructions (T)

161.name: AllocText
161.desc: Free format text related to a specific AllocAccount (79) .

162.name: SettlInstID
162.desc: Unique identifier for Settlement Instructions record.

164.name: EmailThreadID
164.desc: Unique identifier for an email thread (new and chain of replies)

166.name: SettlLocation
166.desc: Identifies Settlement Depository or Country Code (ISITC spec)

168.name: EffectiveTime
168.desc: Time the details within the message should take effect (always expressed in GMT)

169.name: StandInstDbType
169.desc: Identifies the Standing Instruction database used

170.name: StandInstDbName
170.desc: Name of the Standing Instruction database represented with StandInstDbType (169) (i.e. the Global Custodian's name).

171.name: StandInstDbID
171.desc: Unique identifier used on the Standing Instructions database for the Standing Instructions to be referenced.

173.name: SettlDepositoryCode
173.desc: Broker's account code at the depository (i.e. CEDEL ID for CEDEL, FINS for DTC, or Euroclear ID for Euroclear) if SettlLocation (166) is a depository

174.name: SettlBrkrCode
174.desc: BIC (Bank Identification Code-Swift managed) code of the broker involved (i.e. for multi-company brokerage firms)

175.name: SettlInstCode
175.desc: BIC (Bank Identification Code-Swift managed) code of the institution involved (i.e. for multi-company institution firms)

176.name: SecuritySettlAgentName
176.desc: Name of SettlInstSource's local agent bank if SettlLocation (166) is not a depository

177.name: SecuritySettlAgentCode
177.desc: BIC (Bank Identification Code-Swift managed) code of the SettlInstSource's local agent bank if SettlLocation (166) is not a depository

178.name: SecuritySettlAgentAcctNum
178.desc: SettlInstSource's account number at local agent bank if SettlLocation (166) is not a depository

179.name: SecuritySettlAgentAcctName
179.desc: Name of SettlInstSource's account at local agent bank if SettlLocation (166) is not a depository

180.name: SecuritySettlAgentContactName
180.desc: Name of contact at local agent bank for SettlInstSource's account if SettlLocation (166) is not a depository

181.name: SecuritySettlAgentContactPhone
181.desc: Phone number for contact at local agent bank if SettlLocation (166) is not a depository

182.name: CashSettlAgentName
182.desc: Name of SettlInstSource's local agent bank if SettlDeliveryType (172) =Free

183.name: CashSettlAgentCode
183.desc: BIC (Bank Identification Code-Swift managed) code of the SettlInstSource's local agent bank if SettlDeliveryType (172) =Free

184.name: CashSettlAgentAcctNum
184.desc: SettlInstSource's account number at local agent bank if SettlDeliveryType (172) =Free

185.name: CashSettlAgentAcctName
185.desc: Name of SettlInstSource's account at local agent bank if SettlDeliveryType (172) =Free

186.name: CashSettlAgentContactName
186.desc: Name of contact at local agent bank for SettlInstSource's account if SettlDeliveryType (172) =Free

187.name: CashSettlAgentContactPhone
187.desc: Phone number for contact at local agent bank for SettlInstSource's account if SettlDeliveryType (172) =Free

189.name: BidForwardPoints
189.desc: Bid F/X forward points added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

191.name: OfferForwardPoints
191.desc: Offer F/X forward points added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

192.name: OrderQty2
192.desc: OrderQty of the future part of a F/X swap order.

193.name: FutSettDate2
193.desc: FutSettDate (64) of the future part of a F/X swap order.

195.name: LastForwardPoints
195.desc: F/X forward points added to LastSpotRate (194) . May be a negative value.

196.name: AllocLinkID
196.desc: Can be used to link two different Allocation (J) messages (each with unique AllocID (70) ) together, i.e. for F/X 'Netting' or 'Swaps'. Should be unique.

197.name: AllocLinkType
197.desc: Identifies the type of Allocation (J) linkage when AllocLinkID (196) is used.

198.name: SecondaryOrderID
198.desc: Assigned by the party which accepts the order. Can be used to provide the OrderID (37) used by an exchange or executing system.

199.name: NoIOIQualifiers
199.desc: Number of repeating groups of IOIQualifiers.

200.name: MaturityMonthYear
200.desc: Month and Year of the maturity for SecurityType (167) =FUT or SecurityType (167) =OPT. Format: YYYYMM (i.e. 199903)

201.name: PutOrCall
201.desc: Indicates whether an Option is for a put or call.

204.name: CustomerOrFirm
204.desc: Used for options when delivering the order to an execution system/exchange to specify if the order is for a customer or the firm placing the order itself.

205.name: MaturityDay
205.desc: Day of month used in conjunction with MaturityMonthYear (200) to specify the maturity date for SecurityType (167) =FUT or SecurityType (167) =OPT.

206.name: OptAttribute
206.desc: Can be used for SecurityType (167) =OPT to identify a particular security. Valid values vary by SecurityExchange: For Exchange: MONEP (Paris) L = Long (a.k.a. 'American') S = Short (a.k.a. 'European') For Exchanges: DTB (Frankfurt), HKSE (Hong Kong), and SOFFEX (Zurich) 0-9 = single digit 'version' number assigned by exchange following capital adjustments (0=current, 1=prior, 2=prior to 1, etc).

207.name: SecurityExchange
207.desc: Market used to help identify a security.

208.name: NotifyBrokerOfCredit
208.desc: Indicates whether or not details should be communicated to BrokerOfCredit (92) (i.e. step-in broker).

209.name: AllocHandlInst
209.desc: Indicates how the receiver (i.e. third party) of Allocation (J) message should handle/process the account details.

210.name: MaxShow
210.desc: Maximum number of shares within an order to be shown to other customers (i.e. sent via an Indication of Interest (6) ).

211.name: PegDifference
211.desc: Price difference for a pegged order.
